8:
Of all the Guild's outposts, I hear this 
one is the most secluded. It's a several 
day ride from Palpebra.
12:
Which building do you think's the 
outpost?
16:
The largest. The rest look to be homes 
or small shops.
22:
Boss, I put together a manual that 
should help you keep things running 
when I'm gone. I'll leave it on this 
table.
25:
Sharon... Hardworking to the very 
end…
29:
I wouldn't have to be if you'd get off 
your butt once in a blue moon.
39: My! Are you a new adventurer?
42:
Welcome to the Guild. We've got a 
few low-level quests lined up today, 
including trash pickup, roof repair—
46:
No, um, we're here from the Guild of 
Palpebra. We were hired as security 
detail?
49:
Harumph. HQ's lackeys, huh? Sure 
got here fast.
57:
Now, let's start over. My name is 
Sharon. I'm the one you'll be escorting 
to Palpebra.
60:
I'm sorry about my boss. He's... upset 
about my transfer.
62:
But what are you gonna do? HQ is just
booming with business, and this place 
is... You get the picture.
66:
Yeah. Whatever the opposite of 
"booming with business" is.
70: Then why build an outpost here?
73:
We're the town closest to the 
neighboring country. They're right on 
the other side of Sablewood.
74:
Important quests DO come through 
here, but not often enough to justify 
two employees.
77:
Give me a break. Only reason we 
were able to stay afloat is 'cause you 
did the work of three people.
80:
Boss, that wasn't Guild work. Most of 
the time, I was out maintaining town 
facilities or settling disputes.
89:
Speaking of, I've got a few things left 
I want to take care of. Mind waiting 
a bit before we set out?
95:
It's your last day. You should tie up all 
loose ends.
Is there anything with which we could 
help?
98:
Let's see... I've got some welfare 
paperwork to process, and then... You 
boys could help me clean out the 
forest!
114: I was thinking more, picking up trash...
125:
Sharon. If they overwork you over 
there, come running right back, you 
hear?
139:
Welcome to Palpebra, Sharon! I've 
been waiting for you!
143:
So, what do you have waiting for me, 
Manager?
148:
Manager?! Wait. Lilie, you're a 
manager?
152:
Yep. Manager of the Palpebra Guild 
Headquarters: Adventurer Safety, 
Advertising, and General Quality of 
Life Division, to be exact.
156:
If you're wondering why it's got such 
a long name, it's because the division 
was made for Lilie. Some nepotism 
may or may not have been involved.
163:
Sorry. Give me my new address, and 
I'll stop spilling all your deepest, 
darkest secrets.
168:
Yeah... About that... You know 
Palpebra... Big population, stupid high 
rent... You maaay have to live with 
me for the time being.
172: I gave you months to look for a place!
176: Wait. You don't have a place to stay?!
179:
What if I told you I've got a room 
that's clean, safe, AND comes with 
free meals?
183:
Help out with work, and you won't 
even need to pay rent!
189: Hey! No headhunting at the Guild!
194:
Alk, you are a lifesaver!
And the Guild doesn't have rules 
against taking side jobs.
